<TITLE> No Japan Garden officials in sight </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com)  Japan Garden City officials had not visited their sprawling apartment complex till 6.00pm Friday where a devastating fire claimed seven lives the night before. Contacted over phone, Wahiduzzaman Dulal, managing director of Japan Garden City Ltd, hung up his phone as soon as the bdnews24.com correspondent identified himself. The establishment's director Asaduzzaman Zamil told bdnews24.com, "We were afraid of approaching the residents fearing that something untoward might happen." Asked why the hosepipes did not work when firefighters were trying to douse the fire, Zamil said it happened because the water pump could not be started as the mangement cut off electricty fearing the fire could spread further. "That's why firefighters could not work the hosepipes." He claimed that the building had all kinds of fire extinguishing equipment. "But the tragic accident proved they were inadequate." Japan Garden City in Dhaka's Mohammadpur area has 1803 apartments, of which about 1150 have been handed over. It is estimated that there are over 5,000 residents in the complex. bdnews
